BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Miracle on 34th Street
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20261105T200000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20261105T223000
DTSTAMP:20260715T051231Z
UID:occ-828@atlcal.com
SEQUENCE:0
CATEGORIES:Play
DESCRIPTION:The 1947 holiday classic on stage: a department-store Santa wh
 o insists he's the real thing.\n\nA stage version of the 1947 film about K
 ris Kringle\, an old man hired to play Santa at Macy's who calmly maintain
 s that he is Santa — a claim that eventually lands him in a New York cou
 rtroom with his sanity on trial. Between the skeptical single mother who h
 ired him and her even more skeptical young daughter\, the question of beli
 eving becomes the whole ballgame. From Southside Theatre Guild\, an all-vo
 lunteer community theatre running since 1973.
GEO:33.5672762;-84.5821546
LAST-MODIFIED:20260715T051142Z
LOCATION:Southside Theatre Guild\, 20 W Campbellton St
STATUS:CONFIRMED
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
URL:https://tockify.com/stgevents/detail/1017/1793926800000
END:VEVENT
